Package: reciprocal.health.dynamics
Type: Compendium
Title: Socioeconomic Variations in the Reciprocal Relationships Between
    Diet Quality, Physical Activity, and Body Mass Index
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Siard", "van den Bosch", email = "siardvandenbosch@me.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Research compendium for a random-intercept cross-lagged
    panel study of BMI, physical activity, and fruit and vegetable
    consumption across seven annual waves of the Dutch LISS panel, with
    socioeconomic status as a multigroup moderator. Serves as a worked
    use case for the lissr package (archive access, recipe-driven
    merging, income cleaning and equivalisation) and the weasel package
    (wave-based sample selection, tolerance sensitivity, and attrition
    selectivity diagnostics). No microdata are included.
